This data contains of 17 variables with about 4251 records regarding bank loans. Dataset contains subjects from age 19 to 87 years of age. Their job levels, marital status, education level are specified in the dataset. It contains data for subjects with minimum -3313 balance to highest balance of 71188.

In [23]:
library('ggplot2')
ggplot(data=bankloan,aes(x=age,y=balance,color=marital)) +
geom_point() + facet_grid(education~., scale ='free') +
ylim(0,10000)

Warning message:
Removed 458 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

The data seems to equally distributed fro all three categories and they do .not seem to have any relationship woth each other. This means that age and balance both are independendt variables. Balance in your account does not depend on the age of the subjects present in this dataset. Also we see that the marital status does not affect the balance as balance seems to be equally distributed across all mariatl status.
